"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-culture-culture-news-breakdancing-debut-2024-olympics-social-media-react-1235077219\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByJon Blistein  The Paris 2024Olympicswere clearly saving the best for last - no, not the big finals in basketball, soccer, volleyball, or even the modern pentathlon.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.4196517466997e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are talking about the official debut of Breaking (or breakdancing), which bowed with the women's competition on Friday, Aug. 9.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After an introduction provided by the2024 Olympics' Number One correspondent, Snoop Dogg, B-girls from around the world hit the Olympic stage to duke it out on the dancefloor (the men's competition will be held tomorrow, Aug. 10).\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of anticipation has been building for this moment: The International Committee announced the inclusion of Breaking back in 2020, and there is been aplethora of media coverageabout the new contest since.\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, many were pumped, especially those who recognized how remarkable it was to see a breaking, with its deep ties to hip-hop culture, ascend to the pantheon of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is gonna blow the minds of people that have not seen breaking in a while,\\\" Ice T tweeted.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All Respect to HIPHOP.\\\"\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic BreakDancing starts Today!\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"10am Eastern Time\\u2026 This is gonna blow the minds of people that have not seen breaking in a while\\u2026 \\ud83d\\udca5INCREDIBLE\\ud83d\\udca5 All Respect to HIPHOP.pic.twitter.com/DY7zN3UBOw  Even still, that probably wasn't enough to prepare a lot of people for what a Breaking competition would actually look like.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For some folks, the pleasures were immediate and simple: \\\"Just tuned into breaking and the names alone have me seated,\\\" one person wrote onX, alongside a photo showing that competitors would be using their stage names, not their real names - in this case, the USA's Logistx (Logan Edra) versus Australia's Raygun (Rachael Gunn).\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999591386476139, \"rank\": 4.086295628699613e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999996206234565, \"rank\": 3.767667009994427e-07, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1165373819258361e-30, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}, {\"begin\": 1678, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"score\": 0.9999999999508873, \"rank\": 4.92224080282317e-11, \"text\": \"Rachael\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\"}, {\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.8929709720983873, \"rank\": 0.11801841651014433, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could live all my life and never come up with anything as funny as Raygun, the 36-year-old Australian Olympic breakdancer,\\\" someone elsetweeted.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1165373819258361e-30, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}, {\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.99527570435773, \"rank\": 0.004746701634995465, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another person quipped, \\\"Breakdancing at the Olympics is already amazing simply for the visual of seeing somebody from Lithuania in a durag.\\\"\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"score\": 0.9990293294259699, \"rank\": 0.000772222278569244, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breakdancing at the Olympics is already amazing simply for the visual of seeing somebody from Lithuania in a durag2.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2082, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"score\": 0.9990293294259699, \"rank\": 0.000772222278569244, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcers gotta be reaaaaallllll careful pronouncing that name \\ud83d\\ude02pic.twitter.com/Ro6XW9vbLL  As the opening rounds of the contest got underway, more people chimed in with their reviews, which leaned towards the appreciatively goofy, though not without some snark (hey, it is the internet after all).\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Big disney channel original movie vibe to this olympic break dancing,\\\"someonewrote, while anotheradded, \\\"Dude watching some countries break dancing is probably the funniest stuff you will see all week in literal tears.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2626, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Editor's picksThe 250 Greatest Albums of the 21st Century So FarThe 100 Best TV Episodes of All TimeThe 500 Greatest Albums of All Time100 Best Movies of the 21st Century  While some were more prone to hating, the reality was summed up perfectly by one user whoembracedthe ridiculousness, while also acknowledging the best performers were doing something only seasoned athletes with tons of training could do - in other words, putting on a show worthy of the Olympics: \\\"This Breaking competition is both dope and cringe lol.\\\"\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be fair, these reactions were something many breakers were concerned about in the lead up to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3154, \"to\": 3263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In aninterview withRolling Stone,U.S.\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.9999746692208245, \"rank\": 2.5331088795611687e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"men's B-boy Victor Montalvo acknowledged the diluted nature of an Olympic competition (like many other public breaking competitions): The contest will be more one-on-one, rather than embracing the long history of crew battles, and there were also concerns over what music the IOC would be able, or willing, to license without breaking the bank.\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3311, \"end\": 3316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"B-boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}, {\"begin\": 3317, \"end\": 3323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.255648688400241e-11, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 3324, \"end\": 3332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"score\": 0.9971265717792407, \"rank\": 0.0023560724867981112, \"text\": \"Montalvo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's one of the hardest things,\\\" Montalvo said.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We fell in love with the dancing because we fell in love with the music.\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But when we compete we do not have the music we fell in love with, that made us dance at first.\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Trending StoriesJohn Lithgow Knows J.K. Rowling's Anti-Trans Views Will Now Forever Come Up in 'Every Interview'Kevin Spacey's 'Mental Illness' Should Trigger $29.5 Million Payout, 'House of Cards' Trial Jurors HearBTS Nails Its Comeback With 'Arirang'Top Disaster Response Official Claims He Teleported to a Waffle House  Luckily, as it turns out, it does seem the IOC shelled out a bit for the approximately 400 songs it licensed.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jonathan Schecter, co-founder ofThe Source, kept a running tab of some of the tunes used, including Eric B and Rakim's \\\"Do not Sweat the Technique,\\\" \\\"Blow Your Head\\\" by Fred Wesley and the J.B.'s,, and \\\"Hot Music\\\" by S.O.H.O.\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4295, \"end\": 4303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/License\", \"score\": 0.9976828003533751, \"rank\": 0.0018519372571177515, \"text\": \"licensed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/License\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/License\"}, {\"begin\": 4314, \"end\": 4322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schecter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\"}, {\"begin\": 4416, \"end\": 4421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rakim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rakim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rakim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rakim\"}, {\"begin\": 4474, \"end\": 4485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wesley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Wesley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wesley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wesley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The competition and the music\\u00a0 are both getting stronger as the competition progresses,\\\" Schecter tweeted.\", \"from\": 4529, \"to\": 4636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4622, \"end\": 4630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schecter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schecter_Guitar_Research\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Some very exciting battles, the energy driven by premium uptempo selections.\\\"\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yooo the competition and the music  are both getting stronger as the competition progresses.\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some very exciting battles, the energy driven by premium uptempo selections.Lots of Latin funk and boogaloo.\", \"from\": 4810, \"to\": 4918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Was that a hyped-up version of Ray Barretto's Pastime Paradise?\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4953, \"end\": 4965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Barretto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ray Barretto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Barretto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Barretto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83e\\udd0c\\ud83c\\udffc  We want to hear it.\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Send us a tip using our anonymous form.\", \"from\": 5007, \"to\": 50